          "data": {
            "label": "Regulatory Alert",
            "html": "<div style=\"padding:18px 22px;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(124,58,237,0.07),rgba(79,127,255,0.07));border:1px solid rgba(124,58,237,0.2);border-left:4px solid #7C3AED;border-radius:10px;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;margin-bottom:0\"><div style=\"font-size:10px;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1.5px;color:#7C3AED;margin-bottom:7px\">⚖️ Regulatory Update — Effective March 2026</div><div style=\"font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#1a1a2e;margin-bottom:7px;font-family:Georgia,serif;line-height:1.3\">EU AI Act Article 22 Now Applies to Clinical Decision Support</div><div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#4b5563;line-height:1.65\">All AI systems providing clinical recommendations in EU member states must now maintain a human oversight log, publish model cards, and register in the EU AI Registry. Neurologists using off-label AI tools should review institutional compliance timelines immediately. <strong style=\"color:#1a1a2e\">Penalties: up to €30M or 6% of global annual revenue.</strong></div></div>"
          }
        },
